Welcome to my page on the interwebs!

About Me

I am a Software Engineer and most recently I was working at FlightCar before the technology was acquired by Mercedes-Benz. There I was a member of the full stack team working on everything from APIs to web flows to AWS deployments. I love working across the stack because it keeps me moving and allows me to learn new technologies.

My specialties include Python, Django, Javascript, AngularJS, PostgreSQl, and Ruby.

In addition to my coding skills I have 2 years of business development experience at Thrillcall, a music start-up. There I was in charge of managing and analyzing Thrillcall's concert and artist data. I also focused on maintaining and growing new business relationships with ticket partners to augment Thrillcall's data.

Outside of work I am an avid San Francisco Bay Area sports fan, fantasy football hopeful champion, and currently trying to eat every burger in San Francisco. I also enjoy volunteering at the San Francisco Senior Center at Aquatic Park.

Professional and Side Projects

KidAdmit

A marketplace designed for parents to search and disvcover immediate openings listed by childcare providers.

KidAdmit as a whole connected parents and childcare providers to simplify the application process to preschools.

Technologies: Python, Django, JavaScript, AngularJS, Google Maps API.

FlightCar

One step in the process of lisitng a car for rent on FlightCar.

FlightCar was a service provided a way for people at airports to rent their vehicles to incoming travelers and get free parking and compensation for miles driven by the renter.

Technologies: Python, Django, JavaScript, jQuery.

Ideal.Me

Inspired by an idea from the Social Worker Department at the San Francisco Senior Center at Aquatic Park.

The goal was to have a simple platform for seniors and their respective social worker to track the social, intellectual, and health progress of the senior while at the senior center.

Technologies: Ruby on Rails, JavaScript, jQuery, CanvasJs, Devise, Action Mailer, PostgreSQL.
